    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/381.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Bevan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 1. Inform Department at once of the source of authority for levy of
                    war tax, the per cent of the tax assessed, giving <pb facs="0870" n="754"
                        xml:id="pg_754"/> the basis of the levy and the total amount of the property
                    of American companies on which levy is made, what reasons, if any, there are for
                    selecting the particular nine companies, and the probable effect upon them. This
                    Government cannot consent to the levy of a war tax which is discriminatory or
                    which cannot be upheld as reasonable. Advise Nafarrate that Department will
                    communicate with General Carranza upon this subject and point out to Nafarrate
                    the personal responsibility which he will assume if he attempts to enforce the
                    tax until the matters involved have been adjusted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
